pullRequest.body:
`M` is a scalar matrix if it commutes with every nontrivial transvection (elementary matrix).

Also adds `iff` versions and corrects the names of the lemmas in #7810

Co-authored-by: Eric Wieser <wieser.eric@gmail.com>

```suggestion
theorem mem_range_scalar_of_commute {M : Matrix n n R}
```
since you're already in the `TransvectionStruct` namespace.
Seems like it might be useful to have a version without the condition `i â‰  j` for convenience.
For the forward direction you can replace `stdBasisMatrix i j 1` by any square matrix :)
Surely only if `Î±`is commutative? Or are we already in that case?
Apparently not; my bad!
Now we have `mem_range_scalar_iff_commute_stdBasisMatrix'` for this purpose.

```suggestion
  rewrite [scalar_commute_iff]
  simp
```
I find it convenient to have `simp` simplify it.
Note that mathlib prefers `rw` over `rewrite`
Because `rw [scalar_commute_iff]` didn't close the goal, I used `rewrite` instead.
Does this work as `simp [scalar_commute_iff]`?
Sadly no.
